        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-blue-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span><span><strong>Match your style to your position:</strong> Ahead → close. Behind → open. Even → read your rack strength. Don't play one style regardless of the game state.</span></li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-blue-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span><span><strong>Avoid setups unless you hold the key tile:</strong> Setup plays only work if you'll be the one to exploit the lane. If the key tile is common (S, E, R), assume your opponent has it too.</span></li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-blue-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span><span><strong>Start closing 5 turns before bag empties:</strong> Don't wait until the endgame to play defensively. Gradual closing is harder to punish than sudden board shutdown.</span></li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-blue-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span><span><strong>Dump problem tiles in the transition:</strong> Q, V, W, and duplicate vowels become stuck-tile liabilities. Get them off your rack while exchanges are still possible.</span></li>
      </ul>

